text:
The Commission invites submission of proposals to provide a concise, one-time unclassified report on China’s management of electromagnetic spectrum resources, which should:
Provide an overview of how China manages its electromagnetic spectrum;
Provide an overview of how China leverages its spectrum and its application in technology, economic, and military uses;
Assess China’s military spectrum protocols and standard setting;
Examine global implications of China’s spectrum protocols and standard setting; and
Identify and assess commercial and economic benefits of China’s spectrum leadership.
Proposals must be submitted by 5:00 p.m. (ET) on May 19, 2025.
